        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 12:36PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 1236 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Aurora, or near Boaz, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gadsden, Boaz, Attalla, Sardis City, Walnut Grove, Reece City,
Aurora, Noccalula Falls, Howelton, Crudup, Mountainboro, Rockledge,
and Ramsey.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
